<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Neighbour2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Neighbour,</orth> adj. being in the vicinity: <cit><quote>the n. caves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 830" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 830</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a n. thicket,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>bottom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 79</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>such n. nearness to our blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 119</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>confines,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 124</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>air,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.6.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 6, 27</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>states,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>room,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 212</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>shepherd,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 150</bibl></cit>.
